      "description": "Hellhammer's Paiste setup for the De Mysteriis Dom Sathanas sessions was built on the 2002 series — the professional standard of the early 1990s and a common choice for extreme metal drummers who required cymbals capable of sustaining aggressive playing without cracking or losing tonal character under punishment.\n\nThe Paiste 2002's Swiss-made construction delivers a bright, cutting sound with excellent projection — particularly important in the context of Grieghallen's recording environment, where the cymbals needed to register clearly without being excessively compressed or processed. On tracks like \"De Mysteriis Dom Sathanas\" and \"Life Eternal,\" the cymbal work creates an upper-frequency shimmer that complements the album's cold, atmospheric guitar layers rather than fighting them.\n\nThe 2002 Sound Edge hi-hats are central to the blast beat architecture. The Sound Edge's rippled bottom cymbal creates a tighter, more choked sound when closed — essential for the precise, fast-decaying hi-hat strokes that blast beat drumming requires. At the extreme tempos De Mysteriis demands, hi-hats that accumulate wash obscure the rhythmic picture; the Sound Edge's design prevents this mechanically.\n\nThe RUDE China cymbal (from Paiste's more aggressive line) adds the trashy, violent character that black metal accent work requires — an upward-cutting sound that punctuates riff changes and fill endings with aggression that the 2002 crashes alone cannot provide.",
